      "span_text": "Here, we use zeropadding to preserve the original dimension of the data after the convolution. 2D max-pooling is applied to the data; while this operation is traditionally done to induce invariance to image transformation in computer vision [CITATION_1] , we find that for processing these EEG tasks this operation is beneficial primarily for dimension reduction."
